{{see|mensa}}

==English==
===Etymology 1===
{{L.}} [[mensa]], ''[[table]]''; the organisation promotes itself as a "round-table" society in which differences in the backgrounds of its members are considered irrelevant.
====Proper noun====
{{wikipedia|Mensa International}}
'''Mensa'''

#Mensa international; an organisation for people with very high [[IQ]]s.

====See also====
*[[w:Mensa International|Wikipedia article on Mensa]]
*[http://www.mensa.org/home.php Mensa's website]

===Etymology 2===
Named by the French [[astronomer]] Nicolas Louis de Lacaille in 1763. From {{L.}} ''[[mensa]]'', "table"
====Proper noun====
{{wikipedia|Mensa (constellation)}}
'''Mensa'''

#{{constellation}}: A [[summer]] [[constellation]] of the [[southern]] sky, said to resemble a [[table]].  It lies between the constellations of [[Hydrus]] and [[Volans]].

